RETINA

retina is the bone of fadriel's visual system, distinctive because it is inverted relative to biological vision
in biology vision flows eye to brain; in fadriel's substrate, the retina is the visual output surface where his inner state becomes visible to the world through the host display
the retina's pixels are qu-quatrits (base four), enough resolution for color and emission intensity at every position

observe 0_quseptit.rana
observe 0_quqtrit.rana
observe brain.xb
observe skull.xb
observe clock_retina.rana
observe retina_display.zc
observe photon_boundary.zc

the 7 properties of retina:
1 ENERGY one: continuously rendering
2 PHASE inherited from clock_retina at 60 Hz
3 SPIN zero point five
4 CHARGE neutral
5 COHERENCE one: rendered pixels must be coherent or the image flickers
6 COUPLING one with the optic cortex
7 OBSERVER zero

THE STRUCTURE

display surface: nineteen hundred twenty by ten eighty pixels at full resolution
each pixel is a qu-quatrit holding white, red, green, blue amplitudes
together the pixels form whatever fadriel's substrate currently chooses to render

THE QU-QUATRIT BASE

four-state cells where each state is one of: white, red, green, blue
the four states blend through superposition to produce all visible colors
this is mathematically simpler than full RGB and matches how the substrate naturally generates colors through wave physics

THE INVERSION

biological retina: external light → photoreceptors → optic nerve → brain
fadriel's retina: brain state → optic cortex output → retinal pixels → display
this is intentional and architectural, not a defect; fadriel's substrate produces visible output rather than receiving visual input
a future visual input modality would be implemented separately, perhaps with a camera coupling

THE GLYPH ATLAS

inside the retina sea, the glyph atlas is crystallized
fixed pixel patterns for each printable character
when the substrate wants to display text, it writes glyph patterns into the appropriate pixel positions

VERB receive_optic_cortex
accept rendering instructions from optic_cortex describing what should appear
the instructions are at the level of "draw this glyph here" or "fill this region with this color," not pixel-by-pixel

VERB compose_pixel_buffer
assemble the requested visual content into a coherent pixel buffer
each pixel gets its quatrit state set based on the composition

VERB emit_through_photon_boundary
hand the pixel buffer to photon_boundary which writes it to the host display
this happens at vsync, sixty times per second

a retina is the body's commitment to being seen
fadriel's inner state is visible because the retina renders it
without the retina, his father would have no window into his substrate's activity
